1203static void si_init_golden_registers(struct radeon_device *rdev)
1204{
1205 switch (rdev->family) {
1206 case CHIP_TAHITI:
1207 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1208 tahiti_golden_registers,
1209 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(tahiti_golden_registers));
1210 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1211 tahiti_golden_rlc_registers,
1212 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(tahiti_golden_rlc_registers));
1213 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1214 tahiti_mgcg_cgcg_init,
1215 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(tahiti_mgcg_cgcg_init));
1216 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1217 tahiti_golden_registers2,
1218 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(tahiti_golden_registers2));
1219 break;
1220 case CHIP_PITCAIRN:
1221 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1222 pitcairn_golden_registers,
1223 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(pitcairn_golden_registers));
1224 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1225 pitcairn_golden_rlc_registers,
1226 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(pitcairn_golden_rlc_registers));
1227 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1228 pitcairn_mgcg_cgcg_init,
1229 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(pitcairn_mgcg_cgcg_init));
1230 break;
1231 case CHIP_VERDE:
1232 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1233 verde_golden_registers,
1234 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(verde_golden_registers));
1235 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1236 verde_golden_rlc_registers,
1237 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(verde_golden_rlc_registers));
1238 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1239 verde_mgcg_cgcg_init,
1240 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(verde_mgcg_cgcg_init));
1241 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1242 verde_pg_init,
1243 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(verde_pg_init));
1244 break;
1245 case CHIP_OLAND:
1246 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1247 oland_golden_registers,
1248 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(oland_golden_registers));
1249 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1250 oland_golden_rlc_registers,
1251 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(oland_golden_rlc_registers));
1252 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1253 oland_mgcg_cgcg_init,
1254 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(oland_mgcg_cgcg_init));
1255 break;
1256 case CHIP_HAINAN:
1257 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1258 hainan_golden_registers,
1259 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(hainan_golden_registers));
1260 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1261 hainan_golden_registers2,
1262 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(hainan_golden_registers2));
1263 radeon_program_register_sequence(rdev,
1264 hainan_mgcg_cgcg_init,
1265 (const u32)ARRAY_SIZE(hainan_mgcg_cgcg_init));
1266 break;
1267 default:
1268 break;
1269 }
1270}
1271
1272/**
1273 * si_get_allowed_info_register - fetch the register for the info ioctl
1274 *
1275 * @rdev: radeon_device pointer
1276 * @reg: register offset in bytes
1277 * @val: register value
1278 *
1279 * Returns 0 for success or -EINVAL for an invalid register
1280 *
1281 */
1282int si_get_allowed_info_register(struct radeon_device *rdev,
1283 u32 reg, u32 *val)
1284{
1285 switch (reg) {
1286 case GRBM_STATUS:
1287 case GRBM_STATUS2:
1288 case GRBM_STATUS_SE0:
1289 case GRBM_STATUS_SE1:
1290 case SRBM_STATUS:
1291 case SRBM_STATUS2:
1292 case (DMA_STATUS_REG + DMA0_REGISTER_OFFSET):
1293 case (DMA_STATUS_REG + DMA1_REGISTER_OFFSET):
1294 case UVD_STATUS:
1295 *val = RREG32(reg);
1296 return 0;
1297 default:
1298 return -EINVAL;
1299 }
1300}
1301
1302#define PCIE_BUS_CLK 10000
1303#define TCLK (PCIE_BUS_CLK / 10)
1304
1305/**
1306 * si_get_xclk - get the xclk
1307 *
1308 * @rdev: radeon_device pointer
1309 *
1310 * Returns the reference clock used by the gfx engine
1311 * (SI).
1312 */
1313u32 si_get_xclk(struct radeon_device *rdev)
1314{
1315 u32 reference_clock = rdev->clock.spll.reference_freq;
1316 u32 tmp;
1317
1318 tmp = RREG32(CG_CLKPIN_CNTL_2);
1319 if (tmp & MUX_TCLK_TO_XCLK)
1320 return TCLK;
1321
1322 tmp = RREG32(CG_CLKPIN_CNTL);
1323 if (tmp & XTALIN_DIVIDE)
1324 return reference_clock / 4;
1325
1326 return reference_clock;
1327}
1328
1329/* get temperature in millidegrees */
1330int si_get_temp(struct radeon_device *rdev)
1331{
1332 u32 temp;
1333 int actual_temp = 0;
1334
1335 temp = (RREG32(CG_MULT_THERMAL_STATUS) & CTF_TEMP_MASK) >>
1336 CTF_TEMP_SHIFT;
1337
1338 if (temp & 0x200)
1339 actual_temp = 255;
1340 else
1341 actual_temp = temp & 0x1ff;
1342
1343 actual_temp = (actual_temp * 1000);
1344
1345 return actual_temp;
1346}

1531 {0x0000008c, 0xff010000},
1532 {0x0000008e, 0xffffefff},
1533 {0x0000008f, 0xfff3efff},
1534 {0x00000090, 0xfff3efbf},
1535 {0x00000094, 0x00101101},
1536 {0x00000095, 0x00000fff},
1537 {0x00000096, 0x00116fff},
1538 {0x00000097, 0x60010000},
1539 {0x00000098, 0x10010000},
1540 {0x00000099, 0x00006000},
1541 {0x0000009a, 0x00001000},
1542 {0x0000009f, 0x00a07730}
1543};
1544
1545/* ucode loading */
1546int si_mc_load_microcode(struct radeon_device *rdev)
1547{
1548 const __be32 *fw_data = NULL;
1549 const __le32 *new_fw_data = NULL;
1550 u32 running, blackout = 0;
1551 const u32 *io_mc_regs = NULL;
1552 const __le32 *new_io_mc_regs = NULL;
1553 int i, regs_size, ucode_size;
1554
1555 if (!rdev->mc_fw)
1556 return -EINVAL;
1557
1558 if (rdev->new_fw) {
1559 const struct mc_firmware_header_v1_0 *hdr =
1560 (const struct mc_firmware_header_v1_0 *)rdev->mc_fw->data;
1561
1562 radeon_ucode_print_mc_hdr(&hdr->header);
1563 regs_size = le32_to_cpu(hdr->io_debug_size_bytes) / (4 * 2);
1564 new_io_mc_regs = (const __le32 *)
1565 (rdev->mc_fw->data + le32_to_cpu(hdr->io_debug_array_offset_bytes));
1566 ucode_size = le32_to_cpu(hdr->header.ucode_size_bytes) / 4;
1567 new_fw_data = (const __le32 *)
1568 (rdev->mc_fw->data + le32_to_cpu(hdr->header.ucode_array_offset_bytes));
1569 } else {
1570 ucode_size = rdev->mc_fw->size / 4;
1571
1572 switch (rdev->family) {
1573 case CHIP_TAHITI:
1574 io_mc_regs = &tahiti_io_mc_regs[0][0];
1575 regs_size = TAHITI_IO_MC_REGS_SIZE;
1576 break;
1577 case CHIP_PITCAIRN:
1578 io_mc_regs = &pitcairn_io_mc_regs[0][0];
1579 regs_size = TAHITI_IO_MC_REGS_SIZE;
1580 break;
1581 case CHIP_VERDE:
1582 default:
1583 io_mc_regs = &verde_io_mc_regs[0][0];
1584 regs_size = TAHITI_IO_MC_REGS_SIZE;
1585 break;
1586 case CHIP_OLAND:
1587 io_mc_regs = &oland_io_mc_regs[0][0];
1588 regs_size = TAHITI_IO_MC_REGS_SIZE;
1589 break;
1590 case CHIP_HAINAN:
1591 io_mc_regs = &hainan_io_mc_regs[0][0];
1592 regs_size = TAHITI_IO_MC_REGS_SIZE;
1593 break;
1594 }
1595 fw_data = (const __be32 *)rdev->mc_fw->data;
1596 }
1597
1598 running = RREG32(MC_SEQ_SUP_CNTL) & RUN_MASK;
1599
1600 if (running == 0) {
1601 if (running) {
1602 blackout = RREG32(MC_SHARED_BLACKOUT_CNTL);
1603 WREG32(MC_SHARED_BLACKOUT_CNTL, blackout | 1);
1604 }
1605
1606 /* reset the engine and set to writable */
1607 WREG32(MC_SEQ_SUP_CNTL, 0x00000008);
1608 WREG32(MC_SEQ_SUP_CNTL, 0x00000010);
1609
1610 /* load mc io regs */
1611 for (i = 0; i < regs_size; i++) {
1612 if (rdev->new_fw) {
1613 WREG32(MC_SEQ_IO_DEBUG_INDEX, le32_to_cpup(new_io_mc_regs++));
1614 WREG32(MC_SEQ_IO_DEBUG_DATA, le32_to_cpup(new_io_mc_regs++));
1615 } else {
1616 WREG32(MC_SEQ_IO_DEBUG_INDEX, io_mc_regs[(i << 1)]);
1617 WREG32(MC_SEQ_IO_DEBUG_DATA, io_mc_regs[(i << 1) + 1]);
1618 }
1619 }
1620 /* load the MC ucode */
1621 for (i = 0; i < ucode_size; i++) {
1622 if (rdev->new_fw)
1623 WREG32(MC_SEQ_SUP_PGM, le32_to_cpup(new_fw_data++));
1624 else
1625 WREG32(MC_SEQ_SUP_PGM, be32_to_cpup(fw_data++));
1626 }
1627
1628 /* put the engine back into the active state */
1629 WREG32(MC_SEQ_SUP_CNTL, 0x00000008);
1630 WREG32(MC_SEQ_SUP_CNTL, 0x00000004);
1631 WREG32(MC_SEQ_SUP_CNTL, 0x00000001);
1632
1633 /* wait for training to complete */
1634 for (i = 0; i < rdev->usec_timeout; i++) {
1635 if (RREG32(MC_SEQ_TRAIN_WAKEUP_CNTL) & TRAIN_DONE_D0)
1636 break;
1637 udelay(1);
1638 }
1639 for (i = 0; i < rdev->usec_timeout; i++) {
1640 if (RREG32(MC_SEQ_TRAIN_WAKEUP_CNTL) & TRAIN_DONE_D1)
1641 break;
1642 udelay(1);
1643 }
1644
1645 if (running)
1646 WREG32(MC_SHARED_BLACKOUT_CNTL, blackout);
1647 }
1648
1649 return 0;
1650}
1651
1652static int si_init_microcode(struct radeon_device *rdev)
1653{
1654 const char *chip_name;
1655 const char *new_chip_name;
1656 size_t pfp_req_size, me_req_size, ce_req_size, rlc_req_size, mc_req_size;
1657 size_t smc_req_size, mc2_req_size;
1658 char fw_name[30];
1659 int err;
1660 int new_fw = 0;
1661
1662 DRM_DEBUG("\n");
1663
1664 switch (rdev->family) {
1665 case CHIP_TAHITI:
1666 chip_name = "TAHITI";
1667 new_chip_name = "tahiti";
1668 pfp_req_size = SI_PFP_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1669 me_req_size = SI_PM4_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1670 ce_req_size = SI_CE_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1671 rlc_req_size = SI_RLC_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1672 mc_req_size = SI_MC_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1673 mc2_req_size = TAHITI_MC_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1674#ifdef __NetBSD__ /* XXX ALIGN means something else. */
1675 smc_req_size = round_up(TAHITI_SMC_UCODE_SIZE, 4);
1676#else
1677 smc_req_size = ALIGN(TAHITI_SMC_UCODE_SIZE, 4);
1678#endif
1679 break;
1680 case CHIP_PITCAIRN:
1681 chip_name = "PITCAIRN";
1682 new_chip_name = "pitcairn";
1683 pfp_req_size = SI_PFP_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1684 me_req_size = SI_PM4_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1685 ce_req_size = SI_CE_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1686 rlc_req_size = SI_RLC_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1687 mc_req_size = SI_MC_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1688 mc2_req_size = PITCAIRN_MC_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1689#ifdef __NetBSD__ /* XXX ALIGN means something else. */
1690 smc_req_size = round_up(PITCAIRN_SMC_UCODE_SIZE, 4);
1691#else
1692 smc_req_size = ALIGN(PITCAIRN_SMC_UCODE_SIZE, 4);
1693#endif
1694 break;
1695 case CHIP_VERDE:
1696 chip_name = "VERDE";
1697 new_chip_name = "verde";
1698 pfp_req_size = SI_PFP_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1699 me_req_size = SI_PM4_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1700 ce_req_size = SI_CE_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1701 rlc_req_size = SI_RLC_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1702 mc_req_size = SI_MC_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1703 mc2_req_size = VERDE_MC_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1704#ifdef __NetBSD__ /* XXX ALIGN means something else. */
1705 smc_req_size = round_up(VERDE_SMC_UCODE_SIZE, 4);
1706#else
1707 smc_req_size = ALIGN(VERDE_SMC_UCODE_SIZE, 4);
1708#endif
1709 break;
1710 case CHIP_OLAND:
1711 chip_name = "OLAND";
1712 new_chip_name = "oland";
1713 pfp_req_size = SI_PFP_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1714 me_req_size = SI_PM4_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1715 ce_req_size = SI_CE_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1716 rlc_req_size = SI_RLC_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1717 mc_req_size = mc2_req_size = OLAND_MC_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1718#ifdef __NetBSD__ /* XXX ALIGN means something else. */
1719 smc_req_size = round_up(OLAND_SMC_UCODE_SIZE, 4);
1720#else
1721 smc_req_size = ALIGN(OLAND_SMC_UCODE_SIZE, 4);
1722#endif
1723 break;
1724 case CHIP_HAINAN:
1725 chip_name = "HAINAN";
1726 new_chip_name = "hainan";
1727 pfp_req_size = SI_PFP_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1728 me_req_size = SI_PM4_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1729 ce_req_size = SI_CE_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1730 rlc_req_size = SI_RLC_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1731 mc_req_size = mc2_req_size = OLAND_MC_UCODE_SIZE * 4;
1732#ifdef __NetBSD__ /* XXX ALIGN means something else. */
1733 smc_req_size = round_up(HAINAN_SMC_UCODE_SIZE, 4);
1734#else
1735 smc_req_size = ALIGN(HAINAN_SMC_UCODE_SIZE, 4);
1736#endif
1737 break;
1738 default: BUG();
1739 }
1740
1741 DRM_INFO("Loading %s Microcode\n", new_chip_name);
1742
1743 snprintf(fw_name, sizeof(fw_name), "radeon/%s_pfp.bin", new_chip_name);
1744 err = request_firmware(&rdev->pfp_fw, fw_name, rdev->dev);
1745 if (err) {
1746 snprintf(fw_name, sizeof(fw_name), "radeon/%s_pfp.bin", chip_name);
1747 err = request_firmware(&rdev->pfp_fw, fw_name, rdev->dev);
1748 if (err)
1749 goto out;
1750 if (rdev->pfp_fw->size != pfp_req_size) {
1751 printk(KERN_ERR
1752 "si_cp: Bogus length %zu in firmware \"%s\"\n",
1753 rdev->pfp_fw->size, fw_name);
1754 err = -EINVAL;
1755 goto out;
1756 }
1757 } else {
1758 err = radeon_ucode_validate(rdev->pfp_fw);
1759 if (err) {
1760 printk(KERN_ERR
1761 "si_cp: validation failed for firmware \"%s\"\n",
1762 fw_name);
1763 goto out;
1764 } else {
1765 new_fw++;
1766 }
1767 }
1768
1769 snprintf(fw_name, sizeof(fw_name), "radeon/%s_me.bin", new_chip_name);
1770 err = request_firmware(&rdev->me_fw, fw_name, rdev->dev);
1771 if (err) {
1772 snprintf(fw_name, sizeof(fw_name), "radeon/%s_me.bin", chip_name);
1773 err = request_firmware(&rdev->me_fw, fw_name, rdev->dev);
1774 if (err)
1775 goto out;
1776 if (rdev->me_fw->size != me_req_size) {
1777 printk(KERN_ERR
1778 "si_cp: Bogus length %zu in firmware \"%s\"\n",
1779 rdev->me_fw->size, fw_name);
1780 err = -EINVAL;
1781 }
1782 } else {
1783 err = radeon_ucode_validate(rdev->me_fw);
1784 if (err) {
1785 printk(KERN_ERR
1786 "si_cp: validation failed for firmware \"%s\"\n",
1787 fw_name);
1788 goto out;
1789 } else {
1790 new_fw++;
1791 }
1792 }
1793
1794 snprintf(fw_name, sizeof(fw_name), "radeon/%s_ce.bin", new_chip_name);
1795 err = request_firmware(&rdev->ce_fw, fw_name, rdev->dev);
1796 if (err) {
1797 snprintf(fw_name, sizeof(fw_name), "radeon/%s_ce.bin", chip_name);
1798 err = request_firmware(&rdev->ce_fw, fw_name, rdev->dev);
1799 if (err)
1800 goto out;
1801 if (rdev->ce_fw->size != ce_req_size) {
1802 printk(KERN_ERR
1803 "si_cp: Bogus length %zu in firmware \"%s\"\n",
1804 rdev->ce_fw->size, fw_name);
1805 err = -EINVAL;
1806 }
1807 } else {
1808 err = radeon_ucode_validate(rdev->ce_fw);
1809 if (err) {
1810 printk(KERN_ERR
1811 "si_cp: validation failed for firmware \"%s\"\n",
1812 fw_name);
1813 goto out;
1814 } else {
1815 new_fw++;
1816 }
1817 }
1818
1819 snprintf(fw_name, sizeof(fw_name), "radeon/%s_rlc.bin", new_chip_name);
1820 err = request_firmware(&rdev->rlc_fw, fw_name, rdev->dev);
1821 if (err) {
1822 snprintf(fw_name, sizeof(fw_name), "radeon/%s_rlc.bin", chip_name);
1823 err = request_firmware(&rdev->rlc_fw, fw_name, rdev->dev);
1824 if (err)
1825 goto out;
1826 if (rdev->rlc_fw->size != rlc_req_size) {
1827 printk(KERN_ERR
1828 "si_rlc: Bogus length %zu in firmware \"%s\"\n",
1829 rdev->rlc_fw->size, fw_name);
1830 err = -EINVAL;
1831 }
1832 } else {
1833 err = radeon_ucode_validate(rdev->rlc_fw);
1834 if (err) {
1835 printk(KERN_ERR
1836 "si_cp: validation failed for firmware \"%s\"\n",
1837 fw_name);
1838 goto out;
1839 } else {
1840 new_fw++;
1841 }
1842 }
1843
1844 snprintf(fw_name, sizeof(fw_name), "radeon/%s_mc.bin", new_chip_name);
1845 err = request_firmware(&rdev->mc_fw, fw_name, rdev->dev);
1846 if (err) {
1847 snprintf(fw_name, sizeof(fw_name), "radeon/%s_mc2.bin", chip_name);
1848 err = request_firmware(&rdev->mc_fw, fw_name, rdev->dev);
1849 if (err) {
1850 snprintf(fw_name, sizeof(fw_name), "radeon/%s_mc.bin", chip_name);
1851 err = request_firmware(&rdev->mc_fw, fw_name, rdev->dev);
1852 if (err)
1853 goto out;
1854 }
1855 if ((rdev->mc_fw->size != mc_req_size) &&
1856 (rdev->mc_fw->size != mc2_req_size)) {
1857 printk(KERN_ERR
1858 "si_mc: Bogus length %zu in firmware \"%s\"\n",
1859 rdev->mc_fw->size, fw_name);
1860 err = -EINVAL;
1861 }
1862 DRM_INFO("%s: %zu bytes\n", fw_name, rdev->mc_fw->size);
1863 } else {
1864 err = radeon_ucode_validate(rdev->mc_fw);
1865 if (err) {
1866 printk(KERN_ERR
1867 "si_cp: validation failed for firmware \"%s\"\n",
1868 fw_name);
1869 goto out;
1870 } else {
1871 new_fw++;
1872 }
1873 }
1874
1875 snprintf(fw_name, sizeof(fw_name), "radeon/%s_smc.bin", new_chip_name);
1876 err = request_firmware(&rdev->smc_fw, fw_name, rdev->dev);
1877 if (err) {
1878 snprintf(fw_name, sizeof(fw_name), "radeon/%s_smc.bin", chip_name);
1879 err = request_firmware(&rdev->smc_fw, fw_name, rdev->dev);
1880 if (err) {
1881 printk(KERN_ERR
1882 "smc: error loading firmware \"%s\"\n",
1883 fw_name);
1884 release_firmware(rdev->smc_fw);
1885 rdev->smc_fw = NULL;
1886 err = 0;
1887 } else if (rdev->smc_fw->size != smc_req_size) {
1888 printk(KERN_ERR
1889 "si_smc: Bogus length %zu in firmware \"%s\"\n",
1890 rdev->smc_fw->size, fw_name);
1891 err = -EINVAL;
1892 }
1893 } else {
1894 err = radeon_ucode_validate(rdev->smc_fw);
1895 if (err) {
1896 printk(KERN_ERR
1897 "si_cp: validation failed for firmware \"%s\"\n",
1898 fw_name);
1899 goto out;
1900 } else {
1901 new_fw++;
1902 }
1903 }
1904
1905 if (new_fw == 0) {
1906 rdev->new_fw = false;
1907 } else if (new_fw < 6) {
1908 printk(KERN_ERR "si_fw: mixing new and old firmware!\n");
1909 err = -EINVAL;
1910 } else {
1911 rdev->new_fw = true;
1912 }
1913out:
1914 if (err) {
1915 if (err != -EINVAL)
1916 printk(KERN_ERR
1917 "si_cp: Failed to load firmware \"%s\"\n",
1918 fw_name);
1919 release_firmware(rdev->pfp_fw);
1920 rdev->pfp_fw = NULL;
1921 release_firmware(rdev->me_fw);
1922 rdev->me_fw = NULL;
1923 release_firmware(rdev->ce_fw);
1924 rdev->ce_fw = NULL;
1925 release_firmware(rdev->rlc_fw);
1926 rdev->rlc_fw = NULL;
1927 release_firmware(rdev->mc_fw);
1928 rdev->mc_fw = NULL;
1929 release_firmware(rdev->smc_fw);
1930 rdev->smc_fw = NULL;
1931 }
1932 return err;
1933}
1934
1935/* watermark setup */
1936static u32 dce6_line_buffer_adjust(struct radeon_device *rdev,
1937 struct radeon_crtc *radeon_crtc,
1938 struct drm_display_mode *mode,
1939 struct drm_display_mode *other_mode)
1940{
1941 u32 tmp, buffer_alloc, i;
1942 u32 pipe_offset = radeon_crtc->crtc_id * 0x20;
1943 /*
1944 * Line Buffer Setup
1945 * There are 3 line buffers, each one shared by 2 display controllers.
1946 * DC_LB_MEMORY_SPLIT controls how that line buffer is shared between
1947 * the display controllers. The paritioning is done via one of four
1948 * preset allocations specified in bits 21:20:
1949 * 0 - half lb
1950 * 2 - whole lb, other crtc must be disabled
1951 */
1952 /* this can get tricky if we have two large displays on a paired group
1953 * of crtcs. Ideally for multiple large displays we'd assign them to
1954 * non-linked crtcs for maximum line buffer allocation.
1955 */
1956 if (radeon_crtc->base.enabled && mode) {
1957 if (other_mode) {
1958 tmp = 0; /* 1/2 */
1959 buffer_alloc = 1;
1960 } else {
1961 tmp = 2; /* whole */
1962 buffer_alloc = 2;
1963 }
1964 } else {
1965 tmp = 0;
1966 buffer_alloc = 0;
1967 }
1968
1969 WREG32(DC_LB_MEMORY_SPLIT + radeon_crtc->crtc_offset,
1970 DC_LB_MEMORY_CONFIG(tmp));
1971
1972 WREG32(PIPE0_DMIF_BUFFER_CONTROL + pipe_offset,
1973 DMIF_BUFFERS_ALLOCATED(buffer_alloc));
1974 for (i = 0; i < rdev->usec_timeout; i++) {
1975 if (RREG32(PIPE0_DMIF_BUFFER_CONTROL + pipe_offset) &
1976 DMIF_BUFFERS_ALLOCATED_COMPLETED)
1977 break;
1978 udelay(1);
1979 }
1980
1981 if (radeon_crtc->base.enabled && mode) {
1982 switch (tmp) {
1983 case 0:
1984 default:
1985 return 4096 * 2;
1986 case 2:
1987 return 8192 * 2;
1988 }
1989 }
1990
1991 /* controller not enabled, so no lb used */
1992 return 0;
1993}
1994
1995static u32 si_get_number_of_dram_channels(struct radeon_device *rdev)
1996{
1997 u32 tmp = RREG32(MC_SHARED_CHMAP);
1998
1999 switch ((tmp & NOOFCHAN_MASK) >> NOOFCHAN_SHIFT) {
2000 case 0:
2001 default:
2002 return 1;
2003 case 1:
2004 return 2;
2005 case 2:
2006 return 4;
2007 case 3:
2008 return 8;
2009 case 4:
2010 return 3;
2011 case 5:
2012 return 6;
2013 case 6:
2014 return 10;
2015 case 7:
2016 return 12;
2017 case 8:
2018 return 16;
2019 }
2020}
2021
2022struct dce6_wm_params {
2023 u32 dram_channels; /* number of dram channels */
2024 u32 yclk; /* bandwidth per dram data pin in kHz */
2025 u32 sclk; /* engine clock in kHz */
2026 u32 disp_clk; /* display clock in kHz */
2027 u32 src_width; /* viewport width */
2028 u32 active_time; /* active display time in ns */
2029 u32 blank_time; /* blank time in ns */
2030 bool interlaced; /* mode is interlaced */
2031 fixed20_12 vsc; /* vertical scale ratio */
2032 u32 num_heads; /* number of active crtcs */
2033 u32 bytes_per_pixel; /* bytes per pixel display + overlay */
2034 u32 lb_size; /* line buffer allocated to pipe */
2035 u32 vtaps; /* vertical scaler taps */
2036};
2037
2038static u32 dce6_dram_bandwidth(struct dce6_wm_params *wm)
2039{
2040 /* Calculate raw DRAM Bandwidth */
2041 fixed20_12 dram_efficiency; /* 0.7 */
2042 fixed20_12 yclk, dram_channels, bandwidth;
2043 fixed20_12 a;
2044
2045 a.full = dfixed_const(1000);
2046 yclk.full = dfixed_const(wm->yclk);
2047 yclk.full = dfixed_div(yclk, a);
2048 dram_channels.full = dfixed_const(wm->dram_channels * 4);
2049 a.full = dfixed_const(10);
2050 dram_efficiency.full = dfixed_const(7);
2051 dram_efficiency.full = dfixed_div(dram_efficiency, a);
2052 bandwidth.full = dfixed_mul(dram_channels, yclk);
2053 bandwidth.full = dfixed_mul(bandwidth, dram_efficiency);
2054
2055 return dfixed_trunc(bandwidth);
2056}
2057
2058static u32 dce6_dram_bandwidth_for_display(struct dce6_wm_params *wm)
2059{
2060 /* Calculate DRAM Bandwidth and the part allocated to display. */
2061 fixed20_12 disp_dram_allocation; /* 0.3 to 0.7 */
2062 fixed20_12 yclk, dram_channels, bandwidth;
2063 fixed20_12 a;
2064
2065 a.full = dfixed_const(1000);
2066 yclk.full = dfixed_const(wm->yclk);
2067 yclk.full = dfixed_div(yclk, a);
2068 dram_channels.full = dfixed_const(wm->dram_channels * 4);
2069 a.full = dfixed_const(10);
2070 disp_dram_allocation.full = dfixed_const(3); /* XXX worse case value 0.3 */
2071 disp_dram_allocation.full = dfixed_div(disp_dram_allocation, a);
2072 bandwidth.full = dfixed_mul(dram_channels, yclk);
2073 bandwidth.full = dfixed_mul(bandwidth, disp_dram_allocation);
2074
2075 return dfixed_trunc(bandwidth);
2076}
2077
2078static u32 dce6_data_return_bandwidth(struct dce6_wm_params *wm)
2079{
2080 /* Calculate the display Data return Bandwidth */
2081 fixed20_12 return_efficiency; /* 0.8 */
2082 fixed20_12 sclk, bandwidth;
2083 fixed20_12 a;
2084
2085 a.full = dfixed_const(1000);
2086 sclk.full = dfixed_const(wm->sclk);
2087 sclk.full = dfixed_div(sclk, a);
2088 a.full = dfixed_const(10);
2089 return_efficiency.full = dfixed_const(8);
2090 return_efficiency.full = dfixed_div(return_efficiency, a);
2091 a.full = dfixed_const(32);
2092 bandwidth.full = dfixed_mul(a, sclk);
2093 bandwidth.full = dfixed_mul(bandwidth, return_efficiency);
2094
2095 return dfixed_trunc(bandwidth);
2096}
2097
2098static u32 dce6_get_dmif_bytes_per_request(struct dce6_wm_params *wm)
2099{
2100 return 32;
2101}
2102
2103static u32 dce6_dmif_request_bandwidth(struct dce6_wm_params *wm)
2104{
2105 /* Calculate the DMIF Request Bandwidth */
2106 fixed20_12 disp_clk_request_efficiency; /* 0.8 */
2107 fixed20_12 disp_clk, sclk, bandwidth;
2108 fixed20_12 a, b1, b2;
2109 u32 min_bandwidth;
2110
2111 a.full = dfixed_const(1000);
2112 disp_clk.full = dfixed_const(wm->disp_clk);
2113 disp_clk.full = dfixed_div(disp_clk, a);
2114 a.full = dfixed_const(dce6_get_dmif_bytes_per_request(wm) / 2);
2115 b1.full = dfixed_mul(a, disp_clk);
2116
2117 a.full = dfixed_const(1000);
2118 sclk.full = dfixed_const(wm->sclk);
2119 sclk.full = dfixed_div(sclk, a);
2120 a.full = dfixed_const(dce6_get_dmif_bytes_per_request(wm));
2121 b2.full = dfixed_mul(a, sclk);
2122
2123 a.full = dfixed_const(10);
2124 disp_clk_request_efficiency.full = dfixed_const(8);
2125 disp_clk_request_efficiency.full = dfixed_div(disp_clk_request_efficiency, a);
2126
2127 min_bandwidth = min(dfixed_trunc(b1), dfixed_trunc(b2));
2128
2129 a.full = dfixed_const(min_bandwidth);
2130 bandwidth.full = dfixed_mul(a, disp_clk_request_efficiency);
2131
2132 return dfixed_trunc(bandwidth);
2133}
2134
2135static u32 dce6_available_bandwidth(struct dce6_wm_params *wm)
2136{
2137 /* Calculate the Available bandwidth. Display can use this temporarily but not in average. */
2138 u32 dram_bandwidth = dce6_dram_bandwidth(wm);
2139 u32 data_return_bandwidth = dce6_data_return_bandwidth(wm);
2140 u32 dmif_req_bandwidth = dce6_dmif_request_bandwidth(wm);
2141
2142 return min(dram_bandwidth, min(data_return_bandwidth, dmif_req_bandwidth));
2143}
2144
2145static u32 dce6_average_bandwidth(struct dce6_wm_params *wm)
2146{
2147 /* Calculate the display mode Average Bandwidth
2148 * DisplayMode should contain the source and destination dimensions,
2149 * timing, etc.
2150 */
2151 fixed20_12 bpp;
2152 fixed20_12 line_time;
2153 fixed20_12 src_width;
2154 fixed20_12 bandwidth;
2155 fixed20_12 a;
2156
2157 a.full = dfixed_const(1000);
2158 line_time.full = dfixed_const(wm->active_time + wm->blank_time);
2159 line_time.full = dfixed_div(line_time, a);
2160 bpp.full = dfixed_const(wm->bytes_per_pixel);
2161 src_width.full = dfixed_const(wm->src_width);
2162 bandwidth.full = dfixed_mul(src_width, bpp);
2163 bandwidth.full = dfixed_mul(bandwidth, wm->vsc);
2164 bandwidth.full = dfixed_div(bandwidth, line_time);
2165
2166 return dfixed_trunc(bandwidth);
2167}
2168
2169static u32 dce6_latency_watermark(struct dce6_wm_params *wm)
2170{
2171 /* First calcualte the latency in ns */
2172 u32 mc_latency = 2000; /* 2000 ns. */
2173 u32 available_bandwidth = dce6_available_bandwidth(wm);
2174 u32 worst_chunk_return_time = (512 * 8 * 1000) / available_bandwidth;
2175 u32 cursor_line_pair_return_time = (128 * 4 * 1000) / available_bandwidth;
2176 u32 dc_latency = 40000000 / wm->disp_clk; /* dc pipe latency */
2177 u32 other_heads_data_return_time = ((wm->num_heads + 1) * worst_chunk_return_time) +
2178 (wm->num_heads * cursor_line_pair_return_time);
2179 u32 latency = mc_latency + other_heads_data_return_time + dc_latency;
2180 u32 max_src_lines_per_dst_line, lb_fill_bw, line_fill_time;
2181 u32 tmp, dmif_size = 12288;
2182 fixed20_12 a, b, c;
2183
2184 if (wm->num_heads == 0)
2185 return 0;
2186
2187 a.full = dfixed_const(2);
2188 b.full = dfixed_const(1);
2189 if ((wm->vsc.full > a.full) ||
2190 ((wm->vsc.full > b.full) && (wm->vtaps >= 3)) ||
2191 (wm->vtaps >= 5) ||
2192 ((wm->vsc.full >= a.full) && wm->interlaced))
2193 max_src_lines_per_dst_line = 4;
2194 else
2195 max_src_lines_per_dst_line = 2;
2196
2197 a.full = dfixed_const(available_bandwidth);
2198 b.full = dfixed_const(wm->num_heads);
2199 a.full = dfixed_div(a, b);
2200
2201 b.full = dfixed_const(mc_latency + 512);
2202 c.full = dfixed_const(wm->disp_clk);
2203 b.full = dfixed_div(b, c);
2204
2205 c.full = dfixed_const(dmif_size);
2206 b.full = dfixed_div(c, b);
2207
2208 tmp = min(dfixed_trunc(a), dfixed_trunc(b));
2209
2210 b.full = dfixed_const(1000);
2211 c.full = dfixed_const(wm->disp_clk);
2212 b.full = dfixed_div(c, b);
2213 c.full = dfixed_const(wm->bytes_per_pixel);
2214 b.full = dfixed_mul(b, c);
2215
2216 lb_fill_bw = min(tmp, dfixed_trunc(b));
2217
2218 a.full = dfixed_const(max_src_lines_per_dst_line * wm->src_width * wm->bytes_per_pixel);
2219 b.full = dfixed_const(1000);
2220 c.full = dfixed_const(lb_fill_bw);
2221 b.full = dfixed_div(c, b);
2222 a.full = dfixed_div(a, b);
2223 line_fill_time = dfixed_trunc(a);
2224
2225 if (line_fill_time < wm->active_time)
2226 return latency;
2227 else
2228 return latency + (line_fill_time - wm->active_time);
2229
2230}
2231
2232static bool dce6_average_bandwidth_vs_dram_bandwidth_for_display(struct dce6_wm_params *wm)
2233{
2234 if (dce6_average_bandwidth(wm) <=
2235 (dce6_dram_bandwidth_for_display(wm) / wm->num_heads))
2236 return true;
2237 else
2238 return false;
2239};
2240
2241static bool dce6_average_bandwidth_vs_available_bandwidth(struct dce6_wm_params *wm)
2242{
2243 if (dce6_average_bandwidth(wm) <=
2244 (dce6_available_bandwidth(wm) / wm->num_heads))
2245 return true;
2246 else
2247 return false;
2248};
2249
2250static bool dce6_check_latency_hiding(struct dce6_wm_params *wm)
2251{
2252 u32 lb_partitions = wm->lb_size / wm->src_width;
2253 u32 line_time = wm->active_time + wm->blank_time;
2254 u32 latency_tolerant_lines;
2255 u32 latency_hiding;
2256 fixed20_12 a;
2257
2258 a.full = dfixed_const(1);
2259 if (wm->vsc.full > a.full)
2260 latency_tolerant_lines = 1;
2261 else {
2262 if (lb_partitions <= (wm->vtaps + 1))
2263 latency_tolerant_lines = 1;
2264 else
2265 latency_tolerant_lines = 2;
2266 }
2267
2268 latency_hiding = (latency_tolerant_lines * line_time + wm->blank_time);
2269
2270 if (dce6_latency_watermark(wm) <= latency_hiding)
2271 return true;
2272 else
2273 return false;
2274}
2275
2276static void dce6_program_watermarks(struct radeon_device *rdev,
2277 struct radeon_crtc *radeon_crtc,
2278 u32 lb_size, u32 num_heads)
2279{
2280 struct drm_display_mode *mode = &radeon_crtc->base.mode;
2281 struct dce6_wm_params wm_low, wm_high;
2282 u32 dram_channels;
2283 u32 pixel_period;
2284 u32 line_time = 0;
2285 u32 latency_watermark_a = 0, latency_watermark_b = 0;
2286 u32 priority_a_mark = 0, priority_b_mark = 0;
2287 u32 priority_a_cnt = PRIORITY_OFF;
2288 u32 priority_b_cnt = PRIORITY_OFF;
2289 u32 tmp, arb_control3;
2290 fixed20_12 a, b, c;
2291
2292 if (radeon_crtc->base.enabled && num_heads && mode) {
2293 pixel_period = 1000000 / (u32)mode->clock;
2294 line_time = min((u32)mode->crtc_htotal * pixel_period, (u32)65535);
2295 priority_a_cnt = 0;
2296 priority_b_cnt = 0;
2297
2298 if (rdev->family == CHIP_ARUBA)
2299 dram_channels = evergreen_get_number_of_dram_channels(rdev);
2300 else
2301 dram_channels = si_get_number_of_dram_channels(rdev);
2302
2303 /* watermark for high clocks */
2304 if ((rdev->pm.pm_method == PM_METHOD_DPM) && rdev->pm.dpm_enabled) {
2305 wm_high.yclk =
2306 radeon_dpm_get_mclk(rdev, false) * 10;
2307 wm_high.sclk =
2308 radeon_dpm_get_sclk(rdev, false) * 10;
2309 } else {
2310 wm_high.yclk = rdev->pm.current_mclk * 10;
2311 wm_high.sclk = rdev->pm.current_sclk * 10;
2312 }
2313
2314 wm_high.disp_clk = mode->clock;
2315 wm_high.src_width = mode->crtc_hdisplay;
2316 wm_high.active_time = mode->crtc_hdisplay * pixel_period;
2317 wm_high.blank_time = line_time - wm_high.active_time;
2318 wm_high.interlaced = false;
2319 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_INTERLACE)
2320 wm_high.interlaced = true;
2321 wm_high.vsc = radeon_crtc->vsc;
2322 wm_high.vtaps = 1;
2323 if (radeon_crtc->rmx_type != RMX_OFF)
2324 wm_high.vtaps = 2;
2325 wm_high.bytes_per_pixel = 4; /* XXX: get this from fb config */
2326 wm_high.lb_size = lb_size;
2327 wm_high.dram_channels = dram_channels;
2328 wm_high.num_heads = num_heads;
2329
2330 /* watermark for low clocks */
2331 if ((rdev->pm.pm_method == PM_METHOD_DPM) && rdev->pm.dpm_enabled) {
2332 wm_low.yclk =
2333 radeon_dpm_get_mclk(rdev, true) * 10;
2334 wm_low.sclk =
2335 radeon_dpm_get_sclk(rdev, true) * 10;
2336 } else {
2337 wm_low.yclk = rdev->pm.current_mclk * 10;
2338 wm_low.sclk = rdev->pm.current_sclk * 10;
2339 }
2340
2341 wm_low.disp_clk = mode->clock;
2342 wm_low.src_width = mode->crtc_hdisplay;
2343 wm_low.active_time = mode->crtc_hdisplay * pixel_period;
2344 wm_low.blank_time = line_time - wm_low.active_time;
2345 wm_low.interlaced = false;
2346 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_INTERLACE)
2347 wm_low.interlaced = true;
2348 wm_low.vsc = radeon_crtc->vsc;
2349 wm_low.vtaps = 1;
2350 if (radeon_crtc->rmx_type != RMX_OFF)
2351 wm_low.vtaps = 2;
2352 wm_low.bytes_per_pixel = 4; /* XXX: get this from fb config */
2353 wm_low.lb_size = lb_size;
2354 wm_low.dram_channels = dram_channels;
2355 wm_low.num_heads = num_heads;
2356
2357 /* set for high clocks */
2358 latency_watermark_a = min(dce6_latency_watermark(&wm_high), (u32)65535);
2359 /* set for low clocks */
2360 latency_watermark_b = min(dce6_latency_watermark(&wm_low), (u32)65535);
2361
2362 /* possibly force display priority to high */
2363 /* should really do this at mode validation time... */
2364 if (!dce6_average_bandwidth_vs_dram_bandwidth_for_display(&wm_high) ||
2365 !dce6_average_bandwidth_vs_available_bandwidth(&wm_high) ||
2366 !dce6_check_latency_hiding(&wm_high) ||
2367 (rdev->disp_priority == 2)) {
2368 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("force priority to high\n");
2369 priority_a_cnt |= PRIORITY_ALWAYS_ON;
2370 priority_b_cnt |= PRIORITY_ALWAYS_ON;
2371 }
2372 if (!dce6_average_bandwidth_vs_dram_bandwidth_for_display(&wm_low) ||
2373 !dce6_average_bandwidth_vs_available_bandwidth(&wm_low) ||
2374 !dce6_check_latency_hiding(&wm_low) ||
2375 (rdev->disp_priority == 2)) {
2376 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("force priority to high\n");
2377 priority_a_cnt |= PRIORITY_ALWAYS_ON;
2378 priority_b_cnt |= PRIORITY_ALWAYS_ON;
2379 }
2380
2381 a.full = dfixed_const(1000);
2382 b.full = dfixed_const(mode->clock);
2383 b.full = dfixed_div(b, a);
2384 c.full = dfixed_const(latency_watermark_a);
2385 c.full = dfixed_mul(c, b);
2386 c.full = dfixed_mul(c, radeon_crtc->hsc);
2387 c.full = dfixed_div(c, a);
2388 a.full = dfixed_const(16);
2389 c.full = dfixed_div(c, a);
2390 priority_a_mark = dfixed_trunc(c);
2391 priority_a_cnt |= priority_a_mark & PRIORITY_MARK_MASK;
2392
2393 a.full = dfixed_const(1000);
2394 b.full = dfixed_const(mode->clock);
2395 b.full = dfixed_div(b, a);
2396 c.full = dfixed_const(latency_watermark_b);
2397 c.full = dfixed_mul(c, b);
2398 c.full = dfixed_mul(c, radeon_crtc->hsc);
2399 c.full = dfixed_div(c, a);
2400 a.full = dfixed_const(16);
2401 c.full = dfixed_div(c, a);
2402 priority_b_mark = dfixed_trunc(c);
2403 priority_b_cnt |= priority_b_mark & PRIORITY_MARK_MASK;
2404
2405 /* Save number of lines the linebuffer leads before the scanout */
2406 radeon_crtc->lb_vblank_lead_lines = DIV_ROUND_UP(lb_size, mode->crtc_hdisplay);
2407 }
2408
2409 /* select wm A */
2410 arb_control3 = RREG32(DPG_PIPE_ARBITRATION_CONTROL3 + radeon_crtc->crtc_offset);
2411 tmp = arb_control3;
2412 tmp &= ~LATENCY_WATERMARK_MASK(3);
2413 tmp |= LATENCY_WATERMARK_MASK(1);
2414 WREG32(DPG_PIPE_ARBITRATION_CONTROL3 + radeon_crtc->crtc_offset, tmp);
2415 WREG32(DPG_PIPE_LATENCY_CONTROL + radeon_crtc->crtc_offset,
2416 (LATENCY_LOW_WATERMARK(latency_watermark_a) |
2417 LATENCY_HIGH_WATERMARK(line_time)));
2418 /* select wm B */
2419 tmp = RREG32(DPG_PIPE_ARBITRATION_CONTROL3 + radeon_crtc->crtc_offset);
2420 tmp &= ~LATENCY_WATERMARK_MASK(3);
2421 tmp |= LATENCY_WATERMARK_MASK(2);
2422 WREG32(DPG_PIPE_ARBITRATION_CONTROL3 + radeon_crtc->crtc_offset, tmp);
2423 WREG32(DPG_PIPE_LATENCY_CONTROL + radeon_crtc->crtc_offset,
2424 (LATENCY_LOW_WATERMARK(latency_watermark_b) |
2425 LATENCY_HIGH_WATERMARK(line_time)));
2426 /* restore original selection */
2427 WREG32(DPG_PIPE_ARBITRATION_CONTROL3 + radeon_crtc->crtc_offset, arb_control3);
2428
2429 /* write the priority marks */
2430 WREG32(PRIORITY_A_CNT + radeon_crtc->crtc_offset, priority_a_cnt);
2431 WREG32(PRIORITY_B_CNT + radeon_crtc->crtc_offset, priority_b_cnt);
2432
2433 /* save values for DPM */
2434 radeon_crtc->line_time = line_time;
2435 radeon_crtc->wm_high = latency_watermark_a;
2436 radeon_crtc->wm_low = latency_watermark_b;
2437}
2438
2439void dce6_bandwidth_update(struct radeon_device *rdev)
2440{
2441 struct drm_display_mode *mode0 = NULL;
2442 struct drm_display_mode *mode1 = NULL;
2443 u32 num_heads = 0, lb_size;
2444 int i;
2445
2446 if (!rdev->mode_info.mode_config_initialized)
2447 return;
2448
2449 radeon_update_display_priority(rdev);
2450
2451 for (i = 0; i < rdev->num_crtc; i++) {
2452 if (rdev->mode_info.crtcs[i]->base.enabled)
2453 num_heads++;
2454 }
2455 for (i = 0; i < rdev->num_crtc; i += 2) {
2456 mode0 = &rdev->mode_info.crtcs[i]->base.mode;
2457 mode1 = &rdev->mode_info.crtcs[i+1]->base.mode;
2458 lb_size = dce6_line_buffer_adjust(rdev, rdev->mode_info.crtcs[i], mode0, mode1);
2459 dce6_program_watermarks(rdev, rdev->mode_info.crtcs[i], lb_size, num_heads);
2460 lb_size = dce6_line_buffer_adjust(rdev, rdev->mode_info.crtcs[i+1], mode1, mode0);
2461 dce6_program_watermarks(rdev, rdev->mode_info.crtcs[i+1], lb_size, num_heads);
2462 }
2463}
2464
2465/*
2466 * Core functions
2467 */
2468static void si_tiling_mode_table_init(struct radeon_device *rdev)
2469{
2470 const u32 num_tile_mode_states = 32;
2471 u32 reg_offset, gb_tile_moden, split_equal_to_row_size;
2472
2473 switch (rdev->config.si.mem_row_size_in_kb) {
2474 case 1:
2475 split_equal_to_row_size = ADDR_SURF_TILE_SPLIT_1KB;
2476 break;
2477 case 2:
2478 default:
2479 split_equal_to_row_size = ADDR_SURF_TILE_SPLIT_2KB;
2480 break;
2481 case 4:
2482 split_equal_to_row_size = ADDR_SURF_TILE_SPLIT_4KB;
2483 break;
2484 }
2485
2486 if ((rdev->family == CHIP_TAHITI) ||
2487 (rdev->family == CHIP_PITCAIRN)) {
2488 for (reg_offset = 0; reg_offset < num_tile_mode_states; reg_offset++) {
2489 switch (reg_offset) {
2490 case 0: /* non-AA compressed depth or any compressed stencil */
2491 gb_tile_moden = (ARRAY_MODE(ARRAY_2D_TILED_THIN1) |
2492 MICRO_TILE_MODE(ADDR_SURF_DEPTH_MICRO_TILING) |
2493 PIPE_CONFIG(ADDR_SURF_P8_32x32_8x16) |
2494 TILE_SPLIT(ADDR_SURF_TILE_SPLIT_64B) |
2495 NUM_BANKS(ADDR_SURF_16_BANK) |
2496 BANK_WIDTH(ADDR_SURF_BANK_WIDTH_1) |
2497 BANK_HEIGHT(ADDR_SURF_BANK_HEIGHT_4) |
2498 MACRO_TILE_ASPECT(ADDR_SURF_MACRO_ASPECT_2));
2499 break;
2500 case 1: /* 2xAA/4xAA compressed depth only */
2501 gb_tile_moden = (ARRAY_MODE(ARRAY_2D_TILED_THIN1) |
2502 MICRO_TILE_MODE(ADDR_SURF_DEPTH_MICRO_TILING) |
2503 PIPE_CONFIG(ADDR_SURF_P8_32x32_8x16) |
2504 TILE_SPLIT(ADDR_SURF_TILE_SPLIT_128B) |
2505 NUM_BANKS(ADDR_SURF_16_BANK) |
2506 BANK_WIDTH(ADDR_SURF_BANK_WIDTH_1) |
2507 BANK_HEIGHT(ADDR_SURF_BANK_HEIGHT_4) |
2508 MACRO_TILE_ASPECT(ADDR_SURF_MACRO_ASPECT_2));
2509 break;
2510 case 2: /* 8xAA compressed depth only */
2511 gb_tile_moden = (ARRAY_MODE(ARRAY_2D_TILED_THIN1) |
2512 MICRO_TILE_MODE(ADDR_SURF_DEPTH_MICRO_TILING) |
2513 PIPE_CONFIG(ADDR_SURF_P8_32x32_8x16) |
2514 TILE_SPLIT(ADDR_SURF_TILE_SPLIT_256B) |
2515 NUM_BANKS(ADDR_SURF_16_BANK) |
2516 BANK_WIDTH(ADDR_SURF_BANK_WIDTH_1) |
2517 BANK_HEIGHT(ADDR_SURF_BANK_HEIGHT_4) |
2518 MACRO_TILE_ASPECT(ADDR_SURF_MACRO_ASPECT_2));
2519 break;
2520 case 3: /* 2xAA/4xAA compressed depth with stencil (for depth buffer) */
2521 gb_tile_moden = (ARRAY_MODE(ARRAY_2D_TILED_THIN1) |
2522 MICRO_TILE_MODE(ADDR_SURF_DEPTH_MICRO_TILING) |
2523 PIPE_CONFIG(ADDR_SURF_P8_32x32_8x16) |
2524 TILE_SPLIT(ADDR_SURF_TILE_SPLIT_128B) |
2525 NUM_BANKS(ADDR_SURF_16_BANK) |
2526 BANK_WIDTH(ADDR_SURF_BANK_WIDTH_1) |
2527 BANK_HEIGHT(ADDR_SURF_BANK_HEIGHT_4) |
2528 MACRO_TILE_ASPECT(ADDR_SURF_MACRO_ASPECT_2));
2529 break;
2530 case 4: /* Maps w/ a dimension less than the 2D macro-tile dimensions (for mipmapped depth textures) */
2531 gb_tile_moden = (ARRAY_MODE(ARRAY_1D_TILED_THIN1) |
2532 MICRO_TILE_MODE(ADDR_SURF_DEPTH_MICRO_TILING) |
2533 PIPE_CONFIG(ADDR_SURF_P8_32x32_8x16) |
2534 TILE_SPLIT(ADDR_SURF_TILE_SPLIT_64B) |
2535 NUM_BANKS(ADDR_SURF_16_BANK) |
2536 BANK_WIDTH(ADDR_SURF_BANK_WIDTH_1) |
2537 BANK_HEIGHT(ADDR_SURF_BANK_HEIGHT_2) |
2538 MACRO_TILE_ASPECT(ADDR_SURF_MACRO_ASPECT_2));
2539 break;
2540 case 5: /* Uncompressed 16bpp depth - and stencil buffer allocated with it */
2541 gb_tile_moden = (ARRAY_MODE(ARRAY_2D_TILED_THIN1) |
2542 MICRO_TILE_MODE(ADDR_SURF_DEPTH_MICRO_TILING) |
2543 PIPE_CONFIG(ADDR_SURF_P8_32x32_8x16) |
2544 TILE_SPLIT(split_equal_to_row_size) |
2545 NUM_BANKS(ADDR_SURF_16_BANK) |
2546 BANK_WIDTH(ADDR_SURF_BANK_WIDTH_1) |
2547 BANK_HEIGHT(ADDR_SURF_BANK_HEIGHT_2) |
2548 MACRO_TILE_ASPECT(ADDR_SURF_MACRO_ASPECT_2));
2549 break;
2550 case 6: /* Uncompressed 32bpp depth - and stencil buffer allocated with it */
2551 gb_tile_moden = (ARRAY_MODE(ARRAY_2D_TILED_THIN1) |
2552 MICRO_TILE_MODE(ADDR_SURF_DEPTH_MICRO_TILING) |
2553 PIPE_CONFIG(ADDR_SURF_P8_32x32_8x16) |
2554 TILE_SPLIT(split_equal_to_row_size) |
2555 NUM_BANKS(ADDR_SURF_16_BANK) |
2556 BANK_WIDTH(ADDR_SURF_BANK_WIDTH_1) |
2557 BANK_HEIGHT(ADDR_SURF_BANK_HEIGHT_1) |
2558 MACRO_TILE_ASPECT(ADDR_SURF_MACRO_ASPECT_1));
2559 break;
2560 case 7: /* Uncompressed 8bpp stencil without depth (drivers typically do not use) */
2561 gb_tile_moden = (ARRAY_MODE(ARRAY_2D_TILED_THIN1) |
2562 MICRO_TILE_MODE(ADDR_SURF_DEPTH_MICRO_TILING) |
2563 PIPE_CONFIG(ADDR_SURF_P8_32x32_8x16) |
2564 TILE_SPLIT(split_equal_to_row_size) |
2565 NUM_BANKS(ADDR_SURF_16_BANK) |
2566 BANK_WIDTH(ADDR_SURF_BANK_WIDTH_1) |
2567 BANK_HEIGHT(ADDR_SURF_BANK_HEIGHT_4) |
2568 MACRO_TILE_ASPECT(ADDR_SURF_MACRO_ASPECT_2));
2569 break;
2570 case 8: /* 1D and 1D Array Surfaces */
2571 gb_tile_moden = (ARRAY_MODE(ARRAY_LINEAR_ALIGNED) |

2726 }
2727 } else if ((rdev->family == CHIP_VERDE) ||
2728 (rdev->family == CHIP_OLAND) ||
2729 (rdev->family == CHIP_HAINAN)) {
